comments: The official statement from Narciso Yepes and the Yepes heirs is that the young Narciso originally composed the piece for his mother when he was about seven years old (c. 1934) and soon thereafter performed it between acts at the Teatro Guerra, in Lorca. This is improbable since Yepes' version has the same melody as and adds nothing new to Estudio para guitarra by Símon Ramírez released in 1900.
